    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-11-14T22:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-11-14T22:00:00-05:00" n="48"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d48">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">825.24/705d: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-11-14T23:00:00-04:00"
                            >November 14, 1942—11 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1380. Your 1952, November 11, 8 p.m.<note n="52" xml:id="d48fn52">Not
                        printed.</note> On August 7 the Under Secretary delivered to Ambassador
                    Michels a memorandum<note n="53" xml:id="d48fn53">Not found in Department
                        files.</note> containing a statement of the military assistance which had
                    been given and which could be given to the Government of Chile by the War and
                    Navy Departments of the United States. The list of items for future delivery was
                    to form the basis of a Lend-Lease Agreement to be signed after Chile had broken
                    relations with the Axis. These lists were immediately made available by
                    Ambassador Michels to his Foreign Office and to General Espinosa. At a later
                    date, Ambassador Michels expressed to the Under Secretary the very great
                    satisfaction <pb facs="0052" n="38" xml:id="pg_38"/> of the Chilean Government
                    with the assistance represented by the lists of matériel.</p>
                <p>You are authorized to inform the appropriate Chilean authorities that the
                    matériel specified in these lists will be provided in accordance with the
                    conditions set forth therein. These conditions have been made known to the
                    Chilean authorities.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
